5: Oh, Gerard! I was just looking for you.
10:
Well met, Alk! Have you urgent need
of the one and only Gerard, of the
House Martel? My lance is at the
ready!
14:
Oh, it's nothing that serious—no
lances required, really!
20:
Actually, we were talking about
going on a vacation to the beach as
a group. We were wondering if you
wanted to come along?
23:
A holiday on the beach! I know
many places that would be suitable
in the vicinity of Palpebra!
27:
We were actually thinking about
taking this vacation elsewhere—a
change of scenery would be
appreciated right about now.
31:
That's right... So, we found this
special tourist resort in the Endless
Blue. Does that sound up your alley?
37:
In the Endless Blue... That is to say, of
course, that you will be engaging in
the act of swimming, no?
41:
Well, yeah, probably! We're going to
the beach, after all. But there are
lots of other things to do there
besides swimming!
45:
I see... Alas, I must pass on this
invitation. I pray you and your
compatriots enjoy your seaside
sojourn.
49:
Huh? What's the matter? There's
nothing to be worried about. It's a
tourist area so there won't be any
monsters nearby or anything.
53:
You misunderstand me! The great
Gerard of House Martel is not so
lily-livered as to balk at the thought
of fighting monsters!
55:
No, it's merely that... Such a place
would...
Abound in water, would it not?
58:
I... I cannot swim! I'm from a small
village in the mountains,
remember?!
62: Is THAT what you were hung up on?
65:
Hmm. Don't you think you should
learn to swim at some point,
though? It's a useful skill.
67:
You might need it to rescue
someone—or what if YOU fall into
the water? You could drown!
71:
Alk... You're right! How could I have
been so mistaken?
74:
"A true knight never shies away from
a challenge!"
Allow me to accompany you! I must
learn to swim!
78:
I must... I WILL! Yes, without a
doubt.
Well, perhaps. Maybe. If possible.
Yes, a definite maybe.
85:
Gerard of House Martel has arrived!
Steel yourself, sea, for I will conquer
you!
89:
That's some mighty big talk for
someone who was shaking in his
boots the whole way here.
94:
Heh, well it looks like he got over that
real quick.
98:
Let's give the guy a break—he's
almost too easy to make fun of.
102:
Gerard, aren't you going to take off
your helmet? It's very hot.
107:
T-take off my helmet, you say? That
would be tantamount to forsaking
my very knighthood!
112:
Look at your outfit! I don't think
there's anything "knightly" about it
left!
114:
Especially not that... inner tube. Is
that how you intend to "conquer the
sea"?
119:
I... I fear that without it, I would be
powerless... against the raging sea...
128:
Hmm, looks like more and more
people are starting to come in.
132:
Forget the sea, it seems the greatest
peril before us lies in the possibility
of losing our way and getting
separated! We should retreat.
137:
That's a shame. I wanted to stay
longer.
142:
Let's just go to a different place on
the beach, then.
145:
This island's full of other beaches,
though some of them might not be
as... fancy as this one here.
150:
Are you referring to the yet
undeveloped area? I thought no one
was allowed to enter there.
154:
Yep. Mostly 'cause there's monsters.
No people though—I'd say that's
perfect for us!
156:
Plus, they say the fish you catch
there are finger-lickin' good. You
can't catch 'em anywhere else.
166:
Gerard, isn't this where you drop
some words of wisdom about the
importance of not breaking the law?
170:
Lots of great seafood here! Fish,
clams... This calls for a barbeque!
Gerard, do you think you can help
with fishing?
176:
Of course! Leave it to me. So long as
I have my trusty inner tube to hold
me afloat, I am unstoppable!
181:
Th-this is a LOT of fish, Gerard, wow! I
didn't expect this much... Looks like
we'll be having a huge feast tonight!
185:
Hah-hah! But of course. You
entrusted this task to none other
than Gerard of House Martel!
Catching a few fish is but child's
play!
188:
Either way, it's a huge help! It's
gonna be real satisfying preparing
all these fish!
191:
It will no doubt be difficult to gut and
scale some of those larger
fish—please allow me to do it! It's the
least I can do.
197:
I suppose Gerard didn't care to
make a distinction between
monsters and fish. Still, his skill is
commendable.
201:
Wait a minute. Is he... planning on
cooking the monsters too?
205:
Don't be silly. That monster was
probably just swallowed up by a
large fish or something. That was
probably the only one. Or... was it?
211:
Alk, Gerard!
Stop what you're doing now!
221:
Hey, we were about to gut that one!
What's the deal, you two?
224:
There could be monsters inside
those! We're not eatin' those!
Gerard, we're talking to you too!
Stop!
228:
Hmm? But Alk tells me he's had
experience cooking monster meat
before!
